OL,4,Cdiscrimination case for #75k
OL,6,FMr Gillespie was advised in September
OL,7,F2022 that his post was at risk of
OL,8,Fredundancy. He was placed in a
OL,9,Fredundancy pool of one.
OL,11,FDuring subsequent redundancy meetings,
OL,12,Fhe claims that comments were made
OL,13,Fregarding the need to get some new
OL,14,Fblood and of the age profile of the
OL,15,Fsenior management team being all of
OL,16,Fone ilk and age. Mr Gillespie was made
OL,17,Fredundant, and his appeal was not
OL,18,Fupheld.
